text: Wele-Nzas Province is a province in Equatorial Guinea. Its capital is Mongomo. Other major cities include Aconibe, Añisoc, and Nsok. Two national parks, Altos de Nsork National Park and Monte Temelón Natural Reserve, are in the province. The city of Mengomeyén is home to the province's main airport, President Obiang Nguema International Airport. ==References== Category:Provinces of Equatorial Guinea
